elements.title: William Rounseville Alger
elements.contents: ... that William Rounseville Alger's (pictured) 1857 Fourth of July speech was so controversial that the city of Boston refused to print it for seven years?

elements.title: Herrscher des Himmels, erhöre das Lallen
elements.contents: ... that Herrscher des Himmels, erhöre das Lallen, a Bach cantata for the Third Day of Christmas, contains the only aria that he newly composed for the oratorio?

elements.title: the bridge
elements.contents: ... that the bridge from which James Bond leapt in No Time to Die is actually an aqueduct?

elements.title: United Tanganyika Party
elements.contents: ... that despite the support of the British authorities, the multi-racial United Tanganyika Party was unsuccessful, with the African-nationalist TANU winning a majority in the 1958–59 election?

elements.title: Tracy Quint
elements.contents: ... that Maine state legislator Tracy Quint introduced a bill that would have banned all COVID-19 vaccination mandates in Maine until 2024?

elements.title: [went] to the people
elements.contents: ... that in 1874, thousands of Russian students "[went] to the people" to agitate the peasantry towards socialism?

elements.title: Nathaniel Fadipe
elements.contents: ... that a 1939 thesis by Nathaniel Fadipe, The Sociology of the Yoruba, was the first sociological study by a black African?

elements.title: Half-Life: Full Life Consequences
